KEY DESIGN POINTS (from the beads — the beads win on any conflict):
- Query hash: canonical planned AST AFTER macro expansion; expand macros →
  typed AST → NFC → sort commutative AND/OR children → preserve
  non-commutative pipeline/seq/except/sort/limit order → canonical field
  aliases → include grain+lane+rank policy → relative-time queries hash the
  DYNAMIC ast (runs store resolved absolute bounds) → sha256 over
  sorted-key compact JSON.
- Two hashes on result sets: membership merkle root AND ordered_rank_hash
  (set equality ≠ rank equality).
- result_sets rows are MANIFESTS (grain, corpus_epoch, member_count,
  merkle root, rank hash, exactness, persistence class); exact members
  durable ONLY for watch/pinned/finding/cohort persistence classes.
- query_edges (operand-of/refines/supersedes/derived-from/same-as) emitted
  from planner/EXPLAIN nodes, never string parsing; acyclicity check on
  insert for supersedes/derived-from.
- Migrate existing SAVED_QUERY assertions: compile+hash each into queries,
  repoint the assertion at query:<hash> (parity test: zero assertions lost).
- ops.db query_runs: exact DDL is in rxdo.3's design field (columns,
  CHECKs, indexes) — implement it as written. RESULT RELATION IS VIRTUAL:
  ops.db NEVER stores full member lists; promotion (pin) materializes a
  member manifest into user.db result_sets. Expired run refs resolve to a
  typed expired-operational-ref carrying (query_hash, archive_epoch) —
  never a silent miss.
- Envelope: SearchEnvelope gains ADDITIVE fields query_run_ref, query_hash,
  result_fingerprint, exactness — every surface returns them. Wire the
  recording hook at the shared execution chokepoint (archive_query + MCP
  safe_call + daemon list/search handlers if no single chokepoint exists
  yet), fire-and-forget queue to the ops writer: NEVER blocks a read,
  drop-on-backpressure with a counter.
- Previews/keystrokes NEVER persisted. @last resolves per
  (workspace, surface=cli) to the newest query_runs row.

SCHEMA REGIME DISCIPLINE (this is the riskiest part — get it right):
- user.db is DURABLE: numbered additive migration under
  storage/sqlite/migrations/user/NNN_*.sql, one PRAGMA user_version step,
  behind a verified backup manifest. Run
  `devtools lab policy schema-versioning` — it must pass. The rxdo.2 bead
  says the v4→v5 bump "MUST batch with other pending user-v5 candidates" —
